</taxonomicName>
group) as the sister group of all other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[735,806,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Tiphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[735,806,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="128">Tiphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Here we propose a restricted concept of 
<taxonomicName box="[1309,1380,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Tiphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1309,1380,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="128">Tiphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that excludes both 
<taxonomicName box="[322,444,188,211]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Acercopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[322,444,188,211]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="128">Acercopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[508,606,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[508,606,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="128">Pionides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This genus will be subject to further revision when the species level taxonomy of the North American fauna is sufficiently well known to permit the proposal of species groups that are demonstrably holophyletic.
</paragraph>
